### Backup and Point-in-Time Recovery

MongoDB Atlas provides continuous backup with point-in-time recovery (PITR) for M10 and above clusters – you can restore to any second within your configured retention window. For self-hosted deployments, `mongodump` provides logical backups while filesystem snapshots with WiredTiger checkpoints provide faster recovery for large databases.

